items.name: Uranium Waste
items.description:
The by-product of consuming Uranium Fuel Rods in a Nuclear Power Plant.
Non-Fissile Uranium can be extracted. Handle with caution.

Caution: HIGHLY Radioactive.

items.name: Plutonium Waste
items.description:
The by-product of consuming Plutonium Fuel Rods in a Nuclear Power Plant.
Must be stored in a safe location. Handle with caution.

Caution: EXTREMELY Radioactive.

items.description:
Used for building.
Good for stable Foundations.

items.name: Silica

Used for crafting.

items.name: Steel Beam
items.description: Primarily used when constructing slightly more advanced buildings.

items.name: Aluminum Ingot

Smelted from Aluminum Scrap, which is refined from Alumina Solution.
Used to produce specialized aluminum-based parts.

items.name: Packaged Turbofuel
items.description: Turbofuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

Used for crafting.
Primarily used to build Power Lines.

items.description:
Used for crafting.
A sturdier and more durable Iron Plate.

Used for crafting.
The moving parts of a motor.

items.name: Compacted Coal
items.description: A much more efficient alternative to Coal. Used as fuel for vehicles and Coal-Powered Generators.

items.name: Rocket Fuel
items.description:
A high-impulse compressed gas fuel.
Can be used as-is to power Fuel-Powered Generators, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles or the Jetpack.

items.description:
Used for crafting.
Primarily used for Pipelines due to its high corrosion resistance.

items.name: Modular Frame

Used for crafting.
A multipurpose building block.

items.name: Screw

Used for crafting.
One of the most basic parts.

items.name: Nitric Acid
items.description: Produced when Nitrogen Gas reacts with Water. Its high corrosiveness and oxidizing properties make it an excellent choice for refinement and fuel production processes.

items.name: Turbofuel
items.description: A more efficient alternative to Fuel. Can be used as-is to generate power, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles.

items.name: Empty Fluid Tank
items.description: Used to package gases and volatile liquids for transportation.

items.name: Crystal Oscillator
items.description: An electronic oscillator circuit that uses the mechanical resonance of a vibrating crystal to create an electrical signal with a precise frequency.

items.name: Motor
items.description: Creates a mechanical force that is used to move things from machines to vehicles.

items.name: Dark Matter Crystal
items.description:
Concentrated Dark Matter Residue that is isolated within a crystalline vessel. This form of containment allows for utilising Dark Matter reliably in other production processes.

Power Usage: 500-1500 MW (1000 MW average).

items.name: Ionized Fuel
items.description:
Fuel that has been ionized, allowing it to deliver incredible output.
Can be used as-is to power Fuel-Powered Generators, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles or the Jetpack.

items.name: Supercomputer
items.description: The next-gen version of a Computer.

items.name: Cooling System
items.description: Keeps advanced parts and buildings from exceeding efficient temperature levels.

items.name: Ficsite Trigon
items.description: The Ficsite Trigon, made from Ficsite Ingots, is perfectly shaped for all construction challenges. It's performance is so exceptional, it basically solved structural engineering.

items.name: Turbo Motor
items.description: A more complex and powerful version of the regular Motor.

items.name: Time Crystal
items.description: Time Crystals are Diamonds that have been reconfigured on a sub-atomic level in the Converter to retain a time-periodic self-organizing structure. This allows them to be used in the development of quantum processing and storage technologies.

items.name: Dark Matter Residue
items.description:
Produced as a by-product of Quantum Encoding processes and alternatively generated in the Converter.

Various fields of science are still debating the nature and properties of Dark Matter. Meanwhile, FICSIT has found several applications for it in space-time manipulation.

items.name: Reanimated SAM
items.description:
The active and contained form of the Strange Alien Matter.

Proper electromagnetic containment is required, as it appears to be able to manipulate the atomic bonds of any matter it comes into contact with.

items.name: Excited Photonic Matter
items.description:
Excited Photonic Matter is essential for all production processes in the Quantum Encoder.

Formed in the Converter by inducing intense photon interactions through exposure to SAM in a high-energy environment.

items.name: Diamonds
items.description:
Synthetic Diamonds produced by exposing Coal to extreme heat and pressure.

Used in the production of Time Crystals and Dark Matter Crystals.

Power Usage: 250-750 MW (500 MW average).

items.name: Alclad Aluminum Sheet
items.description: Used to make products that require high heat conduction or a high specific strength. Thin, lightweight, and highly durable.

items.name: Superposition Oscillator
items.description: An oscillator circuit that uses the mechanical resonance of a vibrating crystal to create a string vibration with a precise frequency. Often used in teleportation technology and dimensional manipulation.

items.name: Neural-Quantum Processor
items.description: The Neural-Quantum Processor utilizes a combination of neural network architecture and quantum computing techniques to achieve unprecedented performance. This technology has enabled some of FICSIT's biggest advancements in artificial intelligence and relativistic engineering.

items.name: AI Expansion Server
items.description:
Project Part #12. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.
Power Usage: 0-2000 MW (1000 MW average).

Growth is the metric by which we measure success.

items.name: Magnetic Field Generator
items.description:
Project Part #7. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

These modular generators use superconducting magnets and vast amounts of electricity to produce a powerful and easily expandable magnetic field.

items.name: SAM Fluctuator
items.description:
The SAM Fluctuator is able to regulate and direct the behaviour of Reanimated SAM through the application of electric charges with varying frequencies.
This control facilitates technologies such as matter-to-energy conversion and spatiotemporal matter manipulation.

items.name: Steel Pipe
items.description: Primarily used when constructing slightly more advanced buildings.

items.name: Fused Modular Frame
items.description: A corrosion-resistant, nitride-hardened, highly-robust-yet-lightweight modular frame.

items.name: Radio Control Unit
items.description: Enhances and directs radio signals.

items.name: Ficsite Ingot
items.description:
Produced by reconstructing other metals on a molecular level using Strange Alien Matter.

Synthesized by FICSIT to be the perfect construction material, and used in the most high-end processes.

items.name: Biochemical Sculptor
items.description:
Project Part #10. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

Years ahead of the competition, this top-of-the-line 3D printer is used for the production of synthetic biological resources.

items.name: Assembly Director System
items.description:
Project Part #6. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

This extremely fast and precise computing system is specifically designed to direct the Project Assembly: Assembly Phase.

items.name: Caterium Ingot
items.description: Smelted from Caterium Ore. Primarily used for advanced electronics.

items.name: Empty Canister
items.description: Used to package fluids for transportation.

items.name: Circuit Board
items.description: Advanced electronics that have a plethora of different uses.

items.name: Plastic
items.description: Versatile and easy to manufacture, this material has a wide range of uses.

items.name: Encased Industrial Beam
items.description:
Simultaneously utilizes the compressive strength of concrete and the tensile strength of steel.
Mostly used as a stable base for constructing buildings.

items.name: Rubber
items.description: A very flexible material that has a lot of friction.

items.name: Polymer Resin
items.description: A by-product of Crude Oil refinement into Fuel. Commonly used to manufacture Plastic and Rubber.

items.name: Heavy Oil Residue
items.description: A by-product of Plastic and Rubber production. Can be further refined into Fuel and Petroleum Coke.

items.name: Petroleum Coke
items.description:
Used for crafting.
A carbon-rich material distilled from Heavy Oil Residue. 
Used as a less efficient Coal replacement.

items.name: Quartz Crystal
items.description: Derived from Raw Quartz. Used in the production of advanced radar technology and high-quality display screens.

items.name: Steel Ingot
items.description: Smelted from a combination of Iron Ore and Coal. Can be made into several parts used in building construction.

items.name: Versatile Framework
items.description: Project Part #2. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

items.name: Packaged Oil
items.description: Crude Oil, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles.

items.name: Packaged Heavy Oil Residue
items.description: Heavy Oil Residue, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles.

items.name: Packaged Water
items.description: Water, packaged for alternative transport.

items.name: Copper Ingot
items.description: Used for crafting the most basic parts.

items.name: Aluminum Scrap
items.description: Refined from Alumina. Can be smelted into Aluminum Ingots for industrial usage.

items.name: Aluminum Casing
items.description: A versatile container cast from Aluminum Ingots.

items.name: Alumina Solution
items.description: Dissolved Alumina, extracted from Bauxite. Can be further refined into Aluminum Scrap for Aluminum Ingot production.

items.name: Computer
items.description: A complex logic machine that is used to control advanced behavior in other machines.

items.name: Heavy Modular Frame
items.description: A more robust multipurpose frame.

items.name: Smart Plating
items.description: Project Part #1. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

items.name: High-Speed Connector
items.description: Connects multiple cables and wires in a very efficient way. Uses a standard pattern, so it has many varied applications.

items.name: Automated Wiring
items.description: Project Part #3. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

items.name: Stator
items.description:
Used for crafting.
The static parts of a motor.

items.name: AI Limiter
items.description: Controls AIs and keeps them from evolving in malicious ways. Super advanced electronics.

items.name: Quickwire
items.description: Caterium's high conductivity and resistance to corrosion make it ideal for small, advanced electronics.

items.name: Modular Engine
items.description: Project Part #4. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

items.name: Adaptive Control Unit
items.description: Project Part #5. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

items.name: Pressure Conversion Cube
items.description: Converts outgoing force into internal pressure. Required to contain unstable, high-energy matter.

items.name: Encased Plutonium Cell
items.description:
Plutonium Pellets encased in concrete.
Used to produce Plutonium Fuel Rods for Nuclear Power production.

Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

items.name: Plutonium Pellet
items.description:
Produced in the Particle Accelerator through conversion of Non-fissile Uranium.
Used to produce Encased Plutonium Cells for Plutonium Fuel Rods.

Power Usage: 250-750 MW (500 MW average).
Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

items.name: Non-Fissile Uranium
items.description:
The Uranium-238 isotope is non-fissile, meaning it cannot be used for nuclear fission. It can, however, be converted into fissile Plutonium in the Particle Accelerator.

Caution: Mildly Radioactive.

items.name: Sulfuric Acid
items.description: Produced by combining Sulfur and Water in a complex reaction. Primarily used in refinement processes and Battery production.

items.name: Copper Powder
items.description:
Ground-up Copper Ingots.
The high natural density of Copper, combined with the granularity of the powder, makes this part perfect for producing Nuclear Pasta in the Particle Accelerator.

items.name: Heat Sink
items.description: Used to dissipate heat faster.

items.name: Electromagnetic Control Rod
items.description: Regulates power output via electromagnetism.

items.name: Nuclear Pasta
items.description:
Project Part #9. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.
Power Usage: 500-1500 MW (1000 MW average).

Nuclear Pasta is extremely dense degenerate matter, formed when extreme pressure forces protons and electrons together into neutrons. It is theorized to exist naturally within the crust of neutron stars.

items.name: Encased Uranium Cell
items.description:
Used to produce Uranium Fuel Rods for Nuclear Power production. Made from Uranium Ore.

Caution: Mildly Radioactive.

items.name: Dissolved Silica
items.description:
Silica dissolved in Water, produced as part of the alternative refinement of Raw Quartz.
The Silica can be extracted from the Water to complete the refinement process.

items.name: Thermal Propulsion Rocket
items.description:
Project Part #8. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

Uses extreme heat to produce the high-pressure plasma required to get Project Assembly into motion.

items.name: Black Powder
items.description: An explosive powder that is commonly used to produce simple explosives.

items.name: Ficsonium
items.description:
Usage and production of this material is strictly prohibited. On Earth, that is. There are no rules in space, only efficiency. 

Power Usage: 500-1500 MW (1000 MW average).

items.name: Singularity Cell
items.description: Used to break down space and time. Required to power Portals.

items.name: Ballistic Warp Drive
items.description:
Project Part #11. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

A large amount of force is required for the Warp Drives to activate, so sticking them to rockets was the logical next step. Additionally, results improved immensely when the observers were further removed from the Warp Drives upon activation.

items.name: Gas Filter
items.description: Filters out toxins and pollutants from the air when used with a Gas Mask.

items.name: Alien Protein
items.description:
Ground-up Alien Remains in a neat little package.
Used for medical purposes and to research alien organisms.

items.name: Blue Power Slug
items.description: A strange slug radiating an unknown weak power.

items.name: Alien DNA Capsule
items.description:
Translates organic chemicals into readable alien genetic information.
Used for researching alien organisms.

Go the extra kilometer! Knowledge is power, and power is just efficiency with fewer steps. Depositing Alien DNA Capsules in the AWESOME Sink provides FICSIT with knowledge, and pioneers with Coupons.

items.name: Mercer Sphere
items.description: A weird alien phenomenon. While the sphere appears liquid, it behaves like a solid and does not have any detectable mass. It seems to somehow interact with and have awareness of its environment.

items.name: Purple Power Slug
items.description: A strange slug radiating a powerful unknown power.

items.name: Yellow Power Slug
items.description: A strange slug radiating an unknown power.

items.name: Smokeless Powder
items.description: An explosive powder that is commonly used to produce modern firearms.

items.name: FICSMAS Wonder Star
items.description: A symbol of appreciation for all the hard work FICSIT has done for its employees. It seems to have an aura of gratitude. Seeing this also means the seasonal event is nearly done, and we can finally get back to Saving The Day.

items.name: FICSMAS Ornament Bundle
items.description: A collection of FICSMAS ornaments and also an eyesore.

items.name: FICSMAS Tree Branch
items.description: This FICSMAS Tree Branch is very different from regular tree branches: it's used to produce parts and buildings during the FICSMAS event, rather than for combustion.

items.name: FICSMAS Wreath
items.description: FICSIT's newest holiday innovation: decorations that can be turned into decorations! Efficiency and waste-conscious design at its best.

items.name: Candy Cane
items.description:
A delicious Candy Cane to be enjoyed during the FICSMAS Holidays.
*Disclaimer: Not for human consumption…

items.name: FICSMAS Actual Snow
items.description: This Actual Snow is made from several chemical elements and experiences 100% like naturally occuring snow after extensive user testing.

items.name: FICSMAS Bow
items.description: A fancy bow. Not for wearing, eating, admiring, Lizard Doggos, humans, aliens, or anything not related to FICSMAS factory production.

items.name: FICSMAS Gift
items.description:
Gifts that have inexplicably fallen from the sky or spawned from a FICSMAS Gift Tree.

Don’t question it—they’re used to produce FICSMAS buildings and parts.

These Gifts are part of the FICSMAS Event, like the calendar in the HUB.

items.name: Red FICSMAS Ornament
items.description: An ornament for making FICSMAS Decorations. An acceptable red.

items.name: Blue FICSMAS Ornament
items.description: An ornament for making FICSMAS Decorations. A mildly pleasing blue.

items.name: Copper FICSMAS Ornament
items.description: An ornament for making FICSMAS Decorations. A slightly dignified copper.

items.name: Iron FICSMAS Ornament
items.description: An ornament for making FICSMAS Decorations. An okay iron.

items.name: Rebar Gun
items.description: An improvised ranged weapon for self-defense. Has to be reloaded after each use.

items.name: Rifle
items.description: A long-range, rapid-fire weapon. Specifically designed to deliver adequate performance within the designated work area.

items.name: Uranium Fuel Rod
items.description:
Used as fuel for Nuclear Power Plants.

Caution: Produces radioactive Uranium Waste when consumed.
Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

items.name: Plutonium Fuel Rod
items.description:
Used as fuel for Nuclear Power Plants.

Caution: Produces radioactive Plutonium Waste when consumed.
Caution: HIGHLY Radioactive.

items.name: Ficsonium Fuel Rod
items.description:
Used as fuel for Nuclear Power Plants.
The power source that put FICSIT on the map. Literally. The crater is still there.

Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

items.name: Explosive Rebar
items.description: Explodes on impact, dealing heavy damage.

items.name: Stun Rebar
items.description:
Electrocutes the target on impact, stunning it for a short time.

Stun Duration: 5 seconds

items.name: Homing Rifle Ammo
items.description:
The bullet guidance system built into this ammunition allows it to accurately hit any target within the reticle area.
Especially useful when dealing with agile threats, or for pioneers who can't be bothered to aim properly.

items.name: Cluster Nobelisk
items.description: Detonates into multiple smaller explosions. Practical for clearing out large areas of vegetation and other inconveniences.

items.name: Nobelisk
items.description: A simple explosive, useful for clearing boulders, vegetation, and other obstacles.

items.name: Gas Nobelisk
items.description: Creates a deadly gas cloud instead of a regular explosion.

items.name: Nuke Nobelisk
items.description:
Uses a nuclear fission reaction to generate a massive explosion.
WARNING: Ensure all FICSIT property is clear of the blast zone before detonation.

items.name: Pulse Nobelisk
items.description: Generates a powerful shockwave instead of a regular explosion.

items.name: Sweet Fireworks
items.description: Has the minimum safety requirements.

items.name: Fancy Fireworks
items.description: Poses acceptable amount of risk to pioneers.

items.name: Sparkly Fireworks
items.description: Keep away from easily distracted pioneers.

items.name: Snowball
items.description: Compressed dihydrogen monoxide crystals for weaponized fun!

items.name: Iron Rebar
items.description: Can be shot using the Rebar Gun for self-defense purposes.

items.name: Hazmat Suit
items.description:
Shields pioneers from the adverse effects of radiation. 
Consumes Iodine-Infused Filters from the pioneer's inventory when worn in radioactive areas.

items.name: Nobelisk Detonator
items.description: A remote-control device used to handle and detonate Nobelisks.

items.name: Portable Miner
items.description:
Automatically extracts a resource when placed on a resource node.
Note: Has limited storage space.

items.name: Xeno-Zapper
items.description: A standard issue self-defense electroshock melee weapon.

items.name: Object Scanner
items.description: Scans the area for a selected item. Beeps at a rate proportional to proximity and direction.

items.name: Hoverpack
items.description:
Power Consumption: 100 MW

Allows pioneers to move vertically and hover in mid-air to improve building efficiency and factory traversal. Wirelessly connects to nearby power connections, such as Power Poles and Buildings, for power consumption.

Slow-Fall: Hold {PlayerMovement_Jump} after losing connection mid-air.
Disable Hoverpack: Double tap {PlayerMovement_Crouch} while hovering.

items.name: Jetpack
items.description:
Allows pioneers to travel through the air with increased control.

Fuel is automatically consumed from the pioneer's inventory to refill the Jetpack while on the ground.
Different fuel types can be used and provide different levels of Jetpack efficiency. The preferred fuel type will be used if available, and can be set in the equipment inventory.

items.name: Xeno-Basher
items.description: A heavy self-defense electroshock melee weapon.

items.name: Chainsaw
items.description:
Clears an area of flora that is too difficult to remove by hand.

Fuel: Biofuel

items.name: Blade Runners
items.description:
An exoskeleton for the lower legs that assists movement, allowing pioneers to sprint faster and jump higher.
Also dampens the impact of landing.

items.name: Zipline
items.description:
Provides faster traversal of factories by allowing pioneers to zip along Power lines.
Activate the Zipline and aim at a nearby Power Line to connect to it.

items.name: Gas Mask
items.description:
Allows pioneers to breathe normally in toxic gas-filled areas.
Consumes Gas Filters from the pioneer's inventory when in use.

items.name: Candy Cane Basher
items.description: Self-defense is now not only fun, but also delicious for the target! Do not lick or consume.

items.name: Factory Cart™
items.description:
The one and only FICSIT Factory Cart™.
Now with special FICSIT-Foundation-only Grip Wheels, for an even smoother and faster factory floor experience!

items.name: Golden Factory Cart™
items.description:
The one and only Golden FICSIT Factory Cart™

You have now officially ascended. 
Go forth now, Master of Spaghetti, God of the Factory, Sinker of Cups, Employee of the Planet... travel in STYLE!

items.name: Shatter Rebar
items.description: Fractures when shot, launching deadly debris with wide spread but limited range.

items.name: Turbo Rifle Ammo
items.description: Lightweight, compact, and volatile. These rounds provide extreme capacity and rate of fire at the cost of accuracy.

items.name: Rifle Ammo
items.description: Standard issue Rifle ammunition, useful for establishing dominance.

items.name: Iron Ore
items.description:
Used for crafting.
The most essential basic resource.

items.name: Water
items.description: It's water.

items.name: Coal
items.description: Mainly used as fuel for vehicles & Coal-Powered Generators, or in Steel production.

items.name: Nitrogen Gas
items.description: Has a variety of uses, including metallurgy, cooling, and Nitric Acid production. On MASSAGE-2 (AB)b, it can be extracted from underground gas wells.

items.name: Sulfur
items.description: Primarily used to produce Black Powder.

items.name: SAM
items.description: Strange Alien Matter, commonly referred to as SAM, doesn't seem to follow the known laws of physics. It whispers of new possibilities.

items.name: Bauxite
items.description: Used to produce Alumina, which can be further refined into the Aluminum Scrap required to produce Aluminum Ingots.

items.name: Caterium Ore
items.description: Smelted into Caterium Ingots, which are primarily used for advanced electronics.

items.name: Copper Ore
items.description:
Used for crafting.
A basic resource primarily used for electricity.

items.name: Raw Quartz
items.description: Can be processed into Quartz Crystals and Silica, which both offer a variety of applications.

items.name: Limestone
items.description:
Used for crafting.
A basic resource primarily used for stable Foundations.

items.name: Uranium
items.description:
A radioactive element. 
Used to produce Encased Uranium Cells for Uranium Fuel Rods.

Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

items.name: Crude Oil
items.description: Refined into all kinds of Oil-based resources, like Fuel and Plastic.

items.name: Medicinal Inhaler
items.description:
Fully restores health when used.

The FICSIT Medicinal Inhaler can be produced from a variety of different ingredients.

items.name: Power Shard
items.description:
Power Slug mucus compressed into a solid crystal-like shard. 
It radiates a strange power.

items.name: Somersloop
items.description: An odd alien object with a mind-bending, yet somehow familiar shape. It emits an unsettling energy.

items.name: Leaves
items.description:
Primarily used as fuel.
Biomass Burners and vehicles can use Leaves for power.

items.name: Wood
items.description:
Primarily used as fuel.
Biomass Burners and vehicles can use Wood for power.

items.name: Biomass
items.description:
Primarily used as fuel.
Biomass Burners and vehicles can use it for power.
Biomass is much more energy-efficient than raw biological matter.

items.name: Solid Biofuel
items.description: The most energy-efficient form of solid Biomass. Can be used as fuel for the Chainsaw.

items.name: Liquid Biofuel
items.description: Liquid Biofuel can be used as-is to generate power, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles.

items.name: Packaged Liquid Biofuel
items.description: Liquid Biofuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

items.name: Packaged Alumina Solution
items.description: Alumina Solution, packaged for alternative transport.

items.name: Packaged Nitrogen Gas
items.description: Nitrogen Gas, packaged for alternative transport.

items.name: Packaged Nitric Acid
items.description: Nitric Acid, packaged for alternative transport.

items.name: Packaged Sulfuric Acid
items.description: Sulfuric Acid, packaged for alternative transport.

items.name: Fabric
items.description:
Used to craft equipment.
Flexible but durable fabric.

items.name: Mycelia
items.description:
Used for crafting.
Biomass Burners and vehicles can also use Mycelia for power.

items.name: Hog Remains
items.description:
The carapace of an alien Hog creature.
Used for MAM research.

items.name: Spitter Remains
items.description:
The remains of a plasma-spitting alien creature.
Used for MAM research.

items.name: Stinger Remains
items.description:
The remains of whatever that creepy thing was.
Used for MAM research.

items.name: Hatcher Remains
items.description:
The shell-like remains of an alien... thing.
Used for MAM research.

items.name: Paleberry
items.description:
Consumable

Eat to restore 1 health segment.

items.name: Beryl Nut
items.description:
Consumable

Eat to restore half a health segment.

items.name: Bacon Agaric
items.description:
Consumable

Eat to restore 2 health segments.

items.name: Parachute
items.description: Slows down your fall when activated in mid-air.

items.name: Alien Power Matrix
items.description:
This intricate condensed-matter matrix is used to enhance the output of the Alien Power Augmenter. 

Initially developed in efforts to create a human-made Somersloop, the Alien Power Matrix cannot sustain the extra-dimensional energy connection on its own. However, it can effectively stabilize the energy stream of the Somersloop.

items.name: FICSIT Coupon
items.description: A special FICSIT bonus program Coupon, obtained through the AWESOME Sink. Can be redeemed in the AWESOME Shop for bonus milestones and rewards.

buildings.name: Constructor
buildings.description:
Crafts 1 part into another part.

Can be automated by feeding component parts in via a Conveyor Belt connected to the input port. The resulting parts can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

buildings.name: Smelter
buildings.description:
Smelts ore into ingots.

Can be automated by feeding ore in via a Conveyor Belt connected to the input port. The resulting ingots can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

buildings.name: Blender
buildings.description:
Blends fluids together or combines them with solid parts in a wide variety of processes.
Head Lift: 10 m
(Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)

Has both Conveyor Belt and Pipeline input and output ports.

buildings.name: Packager
buildings.description:

buildings.name: Converter
buildings.description:
The Converter harnesses Reanimated SAM to enable precise matter and energy transmutation.

Warning: Power usage is very high and unstable.

buildings.name: Particle Accelerator

Uses electromagnetic fields to propel particles to very high speeds and energies. The specific design allows for a variety of processes, including matter generation and conversion.

buildings.name: Quantum Encoder

buildings.name: Manufacturer
buildings.description:
Crafts 3 or 4 parts into another part.

Can be automated by feeding component parts in via Conveyor Belts connected to the input ports. The resulting parts can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

buildings.name: Assembler
buildings.description:
Crafts 2 parts into another part.

Can be automated by feeding component parts in via Conveyor Belts connected to the input ports. The resulting parts can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

buildings.name: Foundry
buildings.description:
Smelts 2 resources into alloy ingots.

Can be automated by feeding ore in via Conveyor Belts connected to the input ports. The resulting ingots can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

buildings.name: FICSMAS Gift Tree
buildings.description:
A festively disguised production building. Reminder: Nothing is ever truly free.

buildables.name: Power Pole Mk.1
buildables.description:
Allows for up to 4 Power Line connections.

Connect Power Poles, Power Generators, and factory buildings with Power Lines to create a power grid. The power grid supplies all connected buildings with power.

buildables.name: Wall Outlet Mk.1
buildables.description:
Functions like a Power Pole, but attaches to a wall.

Allows for up to 4 Power Line connections.

Connect Power Poles, Power Generators and factory buildings with Power Lines to create a power grid. The power grid supplies all connected buildings with power.

buildables.name: The HUB
buildables.description: The heart of your factory. This is where you complete FICSIT milestones to unlock additional schematics for buildings, vehicles, parts, equipment, etc.

buildables.name: Crafting Bench
buildables.description:
Allows you to manually craft a wide range of different parts. 
These parts can then be used to construct various factory buildings, vehicles, and equipment.

buildables.name: Coal-Powered Generator
buildables.description:
Burns Coal to boil Water. The steam produced rotates turbines that generate electricity for the power grid.
Has Conveyor Belt and Pipeline input ports that allow the Coal and Water supply to be automated.

Caution: Always generates power at the set clock speed. Shuts down if fuel requirements are not met.

buildables.name: Pipeline Wall Support
buildables.description:
Attaches to Walls.
Used to connect Pipelines over longer distances.

buildables.name: Pipeline Mk.1
buildables.description:
Transports fluids.
External indicators show flow rate, direction, and volume.
Capacity: 300 m³ of fluid per minute.

buildables.name: Pipeline Junction
buildables.description: Attaches to a Pipeline, allowing it to be split up to 4 ways.

buildables.name: Pipeline Pump Mk.1
buildables.description:
Attaches to a Pipeline to apply Head Lift.
Maximum Head Lift: 20 m
(Allows fluids to be transported 20 m upwards.)

NOTE: Arrows and holograms when building indicate Head Lift direction.
NOTE: Head Lift does not stack, so space between Pumps is recommended.

buildables.name: Fluid Buffer
buildables.description:
Holds up to 400 m³ of fluid.
Has Pipeline input and output ports.

buildables.name: Water Extractor
buildables.description:
Extracts water from the body of water it is built on.
Note: the water needs to be sufficiently deep, and rivers are generally not deep enough.

Default Extraction Rate: 120 m³ of water per minute.
Head Lift: 10 m
(Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)

buildables.name: AWESOME Sink
buildables.description:
Got excess resources? Fear not, for FICSIT does not waste! The newly developed AWESOME Sink turns any and all useful parts into research data just as fast as you can supply them! 
Participating pioneers will be compensated with Coupons that can be spent at the AWESOME Shop.

buildables.name: AWESOME Shop
buildables.description:
Redeem your FICSIT Coupons here! 
For those employees going the extra kilometer we have set aside special bonus milestones and rewards! Get your Coupons in the AWESOME Sink program now!

*No refunds possible.

buildables.name: Quantum Encoder

The Quantum Encoder uses Excited Photonic Matter to produce the most complex of parts, controlling development up to the quantum level.

Warning: Power usage is extremely high and unstable.

buildables.name: Converter
buildables.description:
The Converter harnesses Reanimated SAM to enable precise matter and energy transmutation.

Warning: Power usage is very high and unstable.

Head Lift: 10 m
(Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)

buildables.name: Valve
buildables.description:

Can be attached to a Pipeline.

NOTE: Has an in- and output direction.

buildables.description:

Can be automated by feeding ore in via Conveyor Belts connected to the input ports. The resulting ingots can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

buildables.name: Packager
buildables.description:
Packages and unpackages fluids.
Head Lift: 10 m
(Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)

Contains both Conveyor Belt and Pipeline input and output ports so that a wide range of recipes can be automated.

buildables.name: Miner Mk.2
buildables.description:
Extracts solid resources from the resource node it is built on. 
Default extraction rate is 120 resources per minute. 
Extraction rate varies based on resource node purity. Outputs all extracted resources onto connected Conveyor Belts.

buildables.name: Manufacturer
buildables.description:
Crafts 3 or 4 parts into another part.

Can be automated by feeding component parts in via Conveyor Belts connected to the input ports. The resulting parts can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

buildables.name: Assembler
buildables.description:
Crafts 2 parts into another part.

Can be automated by feeding component parts in via Conveyor Belts connected to the input ports. The resulting parts can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

buildables.name: Particle Accelerator
buildables.description:
Uses electromagnetic fields to propel particles to very high speeds and energies. The specific design allows for a variety of processes, including matter generation and conversion.

Warning: Power usage is extremely high and unstable, and varies per recipe.

buildables.name: Blender
buildables.description:
Blends fluids together or combines them with solid parts in a wide variety of processes.
Head Lift: 10 m
(Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)

Has both Conveyor Belt and Pipeline input and output ports.

buildables.name: Nuclear Power Plant
buildables.description:
Consumes Nuclear Fuel Rods and Water to produce electricity for the power grid.

Produces Nuclear Waste, which is extracted via the Conveyor Belt output.

Caution: Always generates power at the set clock speed. Shuts down if fuel requirements are not met.

buildables.name: Resource Well Extractor
buildables.description:
Collects pressurized resources when placed on the activated sub-nodes of a Resource Well. Does not require power.

Default Extraction Rate: 60 m³ of fluid per minute.
Head Lift: 10 m
(Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)

buildables.name: Resource Well Pressurizer
buildables.description:
Activates a Resource Well by pressurizing the underground resource. Must be placed on a Resource Well.
Once activated, Resource Well Extractors can be placed on the surrounding sub-nodes to extract the resource.
Requires power. Overclocking increases the output potential of the entire Resource Well.

buildables.name: Drone Port
buildables.description:
Functions as home Port to a single Drone, which transports available input back and forth between its home Port and destination Port.
Drone Ports can have one other Port assigned as their transport destination.

The Drone Port interface provides delivery details and allows management of Port connections.

buildables.name: Conveyor Lift Mk.5

Default extraction rate is 240 resources per minute. 
Extraction rate varies based on resource node purity. Outputs all extracted resources onto connected Conveyor Belts.

buildables.description: Transports up to 1200 resources per minute. Used to move resources between buildings.

buildables.name: Conveyor Lift Mk.6
buildables.description: Transports up to 1200 resources per minute. Used to move resources between floors.

buildables.name: Main Portal
buildables.description:
Enables pioneer teleportation between two linked Portals.

Each Portal can only have a single link. 
A link can only be made between a Main and Satellite Portal.

Singularity Cells need to be supplied to the Main Portal and will be consumed to establish and maintain the Portal link.

WARNINGS:
- Massive power draw will occur during start-up and usage.
- Power draw on use increases with travel distance.
- Link start-up will take time. Letting the connection expire is not recommended.
- Failure to deliver sufficient Singularity Cells will cause the link to expire.
- FICSIT does not condone the use of wormhole technology. Any usage of wormhole technology is at the user's own risk.

buildables.name: Blueprint Designer Mk.3
buildables.description:
The Blueprint Designer is used to create custom factory designs and save them as Blueprints.
Blueprints can be accessed from the Blueprint tab of the Build Menu.

Note that buildings can only be placed in the Blueprint Designer if they are fully within the boundary frame.

Dimensions: 48 m x 48 m x 48 m

buildables.name: Block Signal
buildables.description:
Directs the movement of trains to avoid collisions and bottlenecks.

Block Signals can be placed on Railways to create 'Blocks' between them. When a train is occupying one of these Blocks, other trains will be unable to enter it.

Caution: Signals are directional! Trains are unable to move against this direction, so be sure to set up Signals in both directions for bi-directional Railways.

buildables.name: Path Signal
buildables.description:
Directs the movement of trains to avoid collisions and bottlenecks.

Path Signals are advanced signals that are especially useful for bi-directional Railways and complex intersections. They function similarly to Block Signals, but rather than occupying the entire Block, trains can reserve a specific path through it and will only enter the Block if their path allows them to fully pass through.

Caution: Signals are directional! Trains are unable to move against this direction, so be sure to set up Signals in both directions for bi-directional Railways.

buildables.name: Pipeline Mk.2
buildables.description:
Transports fluids.
External indicators show flow rate, direction, and volume.
Capacity: 600 m³ of fluid per minute.

buildables.name: Pipeline Pump Mk.2
buildables.description:
Can be attached to a Pipeline to apply Head Lift.
Maximum Head Lift: 50 m
(Allows fluids to be transported 50 meters upwards.)

NOTE: Arrows and holograms when building indicate Head Lift direction.
NOTE: Head Lift does not stack, so space between Pumps is recommended.

Loading and unloading options can be set by configuring the building.

Needs to be connected to a powered Railway to function.

buildables.name: Power Storage
buildables.description:
Connects to a power grid to store excess power produced. The stored power can be harnessed if power grid consumption exceeds production.

Storage Capacity: 100 MWh (100 MW for 1 hour)
Maximum Charge Rate: 100 MW
Maximum Discharge Rate: Unlimited

buildables.name: Power Tower
buildables.description:

There is an additional power connector at the bottom of the Power Tower to connect it to other buildings, such as Power Poles.

There is an additional power connector at the bottom of the Power Tower to connect it to other buildings, such as Power Poles.

Sends or receives resources to/from vehicles.

Has 48 inventory slots.

Transfers up to 120 stacks per minute to/from docked vehicles. 
Always refuels vehicles if it has access to a matching fuel type.

Guarantees a safe landing.

The Molecular Analysis Machine is used to analyze new and exotic materials found on alien planets.
Through the MAM, R&D will assist pioneers in turning any valuable data into usable research options and new technologies.

buildables.description:

From here resources can be used by the Build Gun and Crafting Stations, as if they were in the pioneer Inventory.

buildables.name: Geothermal Generator
buildables.description:
Harnesses geothermal energy to generate power. Must be built on a Geyser.

Caution: Power production fluctuates.

Power Production:
Impure Geyser: 50-150 MW (100 MW average)
Normal Geyser: 100-300 MW (200 MW average)
Pure Geyser: 200-600 MW (400 MW average)

buildables.name: Drone
buildables.description:
Transports available input back and forth between its home Port and destination Ports. Drone Status and other details can be viewed at a Drone's home Port.
Must be built on a Drone Port.

Has 9 inventory slots.

Can use any fuel type.
Refuels at any of its connected Ports if possible.

buildables.name: Freight Car
buildables.description:
Attaches to an Electric Locomotive or other Freight Car to transport resources. Must be built on a Railway.
Resources are loaded and unloaded at Freight Platforms.
Has a 1600 m³ or 32-slot capacity, depending on whether resources are liquid or solid.

buildables.name: Electric Locomotive
buildables.description:
Moves Freight Cars from station to station.
Requires between 25-110 MW of power to move. 
Must be built on a Railway.

Nicknamed 'Leif' by FICSIT pioneers because of its reliability.

buildables.name: Truck
buildables.description:
Picks up and delivers resources at Truck Stations. This process can be automated. Nicknamed 'The Unit' by FICSIT pioneers because of its massive frame.

Has 48 inventory slots and a built-in Crafting Bench.

Fuel: Any fuel type

buildables.name: Tractor
buildables.description:
Picks up and delivers resources at Truck Stations. This process can be automated. Nicknamed 'Sugarcube' by FICSIT pioneers with the justification “It’s pretty sweet, y’know”.

Has 25 inventory slots and a built-in Crafting Bench.

Fuel: Any fuel type

buildables.name: Explorer
buildables.description:
Traverses rough terrain, including near-vertical surfaces. A fast and nimble exploration vehicle.

Has 12 inventory slots and a built-in Crafting Bench.

Fuel: Any fuel type

buildables.name: Cyber Wagon
buildables.description:
Absolutely indestructible.
Needs no further introduction.
